# Python Project Standards

- Keep scripts simple and readable for coursework/demo use.
- Prefer small, pure helper functions over large inline blocks.
- Use clear variable names and avoid single-letter names except loop counters.
- Validate file and user input with friendly error messages.
- Add docstrings for non-trivial functions (what it does, inputs, outputs).
- Keep output formatting consistent and easy to scan.
- Do not introduce new dependencies unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve existing file paths and data file names unless asked to change them.
